Key Match Events: The match between England and Australia on October 28, 2022, was abandoned due to rain at Melbourne Cricket Ground.
The rain delayed the toss of the England vs Australia Group 1 match and eventually forced the game to be called off.
England and Australia shared a point each due to the match abandonment.
England took the second spot in Group 1 and Australia the number four due to a better net run rate.
Pre-Game Insights: The match was expected to be a crucial encounter for both teams in their pursuit of a semifinal spot.
The pitch in Melbourne had been quite challenging in this World Cup, adding to the anticipation of the match.
Australia's top order, including David Warner and Aaron Finch, had been struggling with form.
England's explosive batting line-up had not fired in the World Cup so far, and they were looking to make amends.
Jos Buttler mentioned before the World Cup that he would like to give Ben Stokes as much responsibility as possible, including giving him the new ball in both games.
Miscellaneous Highlights: The rain threat was a constant concern, keeping everyone on their toes.
